Asea Brown Boveri, the Swiss-Swedish engineering group, is establishing its
first significant joint venture in Ukraine, it said this week, Andrew Baxter
writes.
ABB is taking 51 per cent of a new company, ABB Ukrelektroapparat, which
will produce distribution transformers in Khmelnitzkij, south-east of Kiev.
The remaining 49 per cent will be held by the Ukrainian company
Ukrelektroapparat and the Ukrainian State Property Agency.
The new company will supply industrial companies and electricity utilities
in Ukraine.
